      Makes an instance of TypeVariableName for the given TypeMirror. This form is used internally to avoid infinite recursion in cases like Enum<E extends Enum<E>>. When such a thing is encountered, a TypeVariableName without bounds is made, and that is added to the typeVariables map before looking up the bounds. Then if encountered again while constructing the bounds, this TypeVariableName can be just returned from the map.
